        "---\n",
        "## Section 2: Sparse Retrieval (BM25)\n",
        "\n",
        "**BM25** is a keyword-matching algorithm. It scores documents by how many query terms they contain, weighted by term rarity (IDF). No neural network needed.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 2.1 Thai Tokenization\n",
        "\n",
        "BM25 needs tokenized text. Thai has no spaces between words, so we use `pythainlp` to segment."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 42,
      "id": "149w0n0661l",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "149w0n0661l",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "90d93854-cf2f-476d-f591-89c189a4ba39"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Input:  Watch S3 Ultra กันน้ำได้กี่ ATM ครับ?\n",
            "Tokens: ['Watch', ' ', 'S', '3', ' ', 'Ultra', ' ', 'กันน้ำ', 'ได้', 'กี่', ' ', 'ATM', ' ', 'ครับ', '?']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from pythainlp.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
        "\n",
        "# Demo: tokenize a Thai sentence\n",
        "sample = \"Watch S3 Ultra กันน้ำได้กี่ ATM ครับ?\"\n",
        "tokens = word_tokenize(sample, engine=\"newmm\")\n",
        "print(f\"Input:  {sample}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Tokens: {tokens}\")"
      ]
